### Q13. What is "void type not allowed here" error?

You're trying to use a void method's "return value" which doesn't exist.

```java
public void sendEmail(String to) {
    // sends email
}

public void notifyUser() {
    String result = sendEmail("user@mail.com"); // Error: void type not allowed here
}

// Another case:
System.out.println(sendEmail("test@mail.com")); // Error: void type not allowed here
```

**Why?** Void methods don't return anything, so you can't assign their "result" to a variable or print it.

**Industry example:** In a notification service, if sendSMS() is a void method (just sends, doesn't return status), you cannot do `boolean status = sendSMS(number)`. The method needs to return boolean if you want to capture status.

