## PART 4: MORE RUNTIME EXCEPTIONS

### Q26. What is StringIndexOutOfBoundsException?

Trying to access a character in a String at an invalid index.

```java
String name = "John"; // length = 4, valid indices: 0,1,2,3
char c = name.charAt(5); // StringIndexOutOfBoundsException

String email = "user@mail.com";
String sub = email.substring(20); // StringIndexOutOfBoundsException
```

**Common scenarios:**

```java
String password = "";
char firstChar = password.charAt(0); // Exception - empty string

String code = "ABC";
String part = code.substring(1, 5); // Exception - end index 5 > length 3
```

**Safe access:**
```java
if(name.length() > 5) {
    char c = name.charAt(5);
}

// Or
if(index >= 0 && index < name.length()) {
    char c = name.charAt(index);
}
```

**Industry example:** In an OTP validation service, if you try to extract the first 4 characters from user input using `otp.substring(0, 4)` but user entered only 3 digits, you get StringIndexOutOfBoundsException. Always check: `if(otp.length() >= 4)` first.

