    System.out.println("SQL state: " + e.getSQLState());
    System.out.println("Message: " + e.getMessage());
}
```

**Industry example:** In user registration, when inserting new user, if email already exists (unique constraint), SQLException is thrown. You catch it and check error code to determine if it's duplicate key error, then show user: "Email already registered. Please use different email."

