### Q61. What is @ExceptionHandler annotation?

@ExceptionHandler marks a method to handle specific exception types.

```java
@ControllerAdvice
public class GlobalExceptionHandler {
    
    // Handle specific exception
    @ExceptionHandler(UserNotFoundException.class)
    public ResponseEntity<String> handleUserNotFound(UserNotFoundException e) {
        return ResponseEntity.status(404).body(e.getMessage());
    }
    
    // Handle multiple exceptions
    @ExceptionHandler({SQLException.class, DataAccessException.class})
    public ResponseEntity<String> handleDatabaseErrors(Exception e) {
        return ResponseEntity.status(500).body("Database error occurred");
    }
    
    // Handle all exceptions
    @ExceptionHandler(Exception.class)
    public ResponseEntity<String> handleAllExceptions(Exception e) {
        return ResponseEntity.status(500).body("An error occurred");
    }
}
