### Q65. How do we handle database exceptions (DataAccessException)?

Spring's DataAccessException is thrown for database-related errors. Handle it globally to avoid exposing database details to clients.

**Handling DataAccessException:**
```java
@ControllerAdvice
public class GlobalExceptionHandler {
    
    @ExceptionHandler(DataAccessException.class)
    public ResponseEntity<ErrorResponse> handleDatabaseErrors(
        DataAccessException e,
        WebRequest request
    ) {
        ErrorResponse error = new ErrorResponse(
            HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR.value(),
            "Database operation failed. Please try again later.",
            request.getDescription(false).replace("uri=", "")
        );
        
        // Log actual error for debugging (don't expose to client)
        System.err.println("Database error: " + e.getMessage());
        
        return new ResponseEntity<>(error, HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);
    }
}
```

**Handling specific database exceptions:**
```java
@ExceptionHandler(DataIntegrityViolationException.class)
public ResponseEntity<ErrorResponse> handleDataIntegrityViolation(
    DataIntegrityViolationException e,
    WebRequest request
) {
    String message = "Data integrity constraint violated";
    
    // Check if it's a duplicate key error
    if(e.getMessage().contains("Duplicate entry")) {
        message = "Record already exists with this information";
    }
    
    ErrorResponse error = new ErrorResponse(
        HttpStatus.CONFLICT.value(),
        message,
        request.getDescription(false).replace("uri=", "")
    );
    
    return new ResponseEntity<>(error, HttpStatus.CONFLICT);
}
```

**Why hide database details?**
```java
// Bad - exposes database structure
"Error: Duplicate entry 'john@example.com' for key 'users.email_UNIQUE'"

// Good - user-friendly message
"Email already registered. Please use a different email."
```

**Industry example:** In PerformanceTrack, when saving a goal with duplicate title (if you have unique constraint), DataIntegrityViolationException is thrown. Instead of showing "Duplicate entry 'Q1 Sales Target' for key 'goals.title_UNIQUE'", you show "A goal with this title already exists. Please use a different title."

