### Q69. How do we handle exceptions in multi-threaded environments?

Exceptions in separate threads don't propagate to the main thread. You need special handling.

**Problem - Exception lost in thread:**
```java
public void processOrders() {
    Thread thread = new Thread(() -> {
        int x = 10 / 0; // ArithmeticException thrown
    });
    thread.start();
    
    // Exception in thread doesn't affect main thread
    // Main thread continues, exception is just printed to console
}
```

**Solution 1 - Using ExecutorService with Future:**
```java
ExecutorService executor = Executors.newFixedThreadPool(5);

Future<String> future = executor.submit(() -> {
    if(someCondition) {
        throw new CustomException("Error in thread");
    }
    return "Success";
});

try {
    String result = future.get(); // This will throw exception if task failed
} catch(ExecutionException e) {
    Throwable cause = e.getCause(); // Get the actual exception
    if(cause instanceof CustomException) {
        // Handle CustomException
    }
} catch(InterruptedException e) {
    // Handle interruption
}
```

**Solution 2 - Using Thread.UncaughtExceptionHandler:**
```java
Thread thread = new Thread(() -> {
    int x = 10 / 0; // Will be caught by handler
});

thread.setUncaughtExceptionHandler((t, e) -> {
    logger.error("Exception in thread " + t.getName(), e);
    // Send alert, save to database, etc.
});

thread.start();
```

**Solution 3 - CompletableFuture (modern approach):**
```java
CompletableFuture.supplyAsync(() -> {
    if(someError) {
        throw new CustomException("Error");
    }
    return processData();
})
.exceptionally(e -> {
    logger.error("Async processing failed", e);
    return defaultValue; // Fallback value
})
.thenAccept(result -> {
    // Use result
});
```

**Industry example:** In PerformanceTrack, when generating department-wise analytics report, you process each department in parallel threads. If one thread fails (maybe data corruption for HR department), you don't want entire report to fail. You use CompletableFuture, catch exception for failed department, log it, and continue with other departments. Final report shows "HR: Data unavailable" instead of crashing.

