        // Save failed email to retry queue
        retryQueue.add(new FailedEmail(to, message));
    }
}
```

**Industry example:** In PerformanceTrack, when a goal is approved, you send notification emails to employee and manager asynchronously. If email service is down, you don't want goal approval to fail. You use @Async with try-catch inside method, catch exception, log "Email notification failed for goal ID: 123", and save notification to retry queue for later delivery.

