### Q78. How do we handle exceptions in REST API with proper HTTP status codes?

Different exceptions should map to different HTTP status codes with meaningful error responses.

**Complete REST exception handling:**
```java
@RestControllerAdvice
public class RestExceptionHandler {
    
    // 400 Bad Request - Client error
    @ExceptionHandler(MethodArgumentNotValidException.class)
    @ResponseStatus(HttpStatus.BAD_REQUEST)
    public ErrorResponse handleValidationErrors(MethodArgumentNotValidException e) {
        ErrorResponse error = new ErrorResponse(
            400,
            "Validation failed",
            LocalDateTime.now()
        );
        
        e.getBindingResult().getFieldErrors().forEach(fieldError -> 
            error.addValidationError(fieldError.getField(), fieldError.getDefaultMessage())
        );
        
        return error;
    }
    
    // 401 Unauthorized - Authentication required
    @ExceptionHandler(AuthenticationException.class)
    @ResponseStatus(HttpStatus.UNAUTHORIZED)
    public ErrorResponse handleAuthenticationError(AuthenticationException e) {
        return new ErrorResponse(401, "Authentication required", LocalDateTime.now());
    }
    
    // 403 Forbidden - Authenticated but not authorized
    @ExceptionHandler(AccessDeniedException.class)
    @ResponseStatus(HttpStatus.FORBIDDEN)
    public ErrorResponse handleAccessDenied(AccessDeniedException e) {
        return new ErrorResponse(403, "Access denied: " + e.getMessage(), LocalDateTime.now());
    }
    
    // 404 Not Found - Resource doesn't exist
    @ExceptionHandler(ResourceNotFoundException.class)
    @ResponseStatus(HttpStatus.NOT_FOUND)
    public ErrorResponse handleNotFound(ResourceNotFoundException e) {
        return new ErrorResponse(404, e.getMessage(), LocalDateTime.now());
    }
    
    // 409 Conflict - Resource already exists or state conflict
    @ExceptionHandler(DuplicateResourceException.class)
    @ResponseStatus(HttpStatus.CONFLICT)
    public ErrorResponse handleDuplicate(DuplicateResourceException e) {
        return new ErrorResponse(409, e.getMessage(), LocalDateTime.now());
    }
    
    // 422 Unprocessable Entity - Valid syntax but semantic errors
    @ExceptionHandler(BusinessValidationException.class)
    @ResponseStatus(HttpStatus.UNPROCESSABLE_ENTITY)
    public ErrorResponse handleBusinessValidation(BusinessValidationException e) {
        return new ErrorResponse(422, e.getMessage(), LocalDateTime.now());
    }
    
    // 500 Internal Server Error - Unexpected errors
    @ExceptionHandler(Exception.class)
    @ResponseStatus(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR)
    public ErrorResponse handleInternalError(Exception e) {
        logger.error("Unexpected error", e);
        return new ErrorResponse(
            500, 
            "An unexpected error occurred. Please contact support.", 
            LocalDateTime.now()
        );
    }
    
    // 503 Service Unavailable - External service down
    @ExceptionHandler(ServiceUnavailableException.class)
    @ResponseStatus(HttpStatus.SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE)
    public ErrorResponse handleServiceUnavailable(ServiceUnavailableException e) {
        return new ErrorResponse(503, e.getMessage(), LocalDateTime.now());
    }
}
```

**Enhanced error response structure:**
```java
public class ErrorResponse {
    private int status;
    private String message;
    private LocalDateTime timestamp;
    private String path;
    private List<ValidationError> validationErrors;
    
    public static class ValidationError {
        private String field;
        private String message;
        
        // Constructor, getters, setters
    }
    
    public void addValidationError(String field, String message) {
        if(validationErrors == null) {
            validationErrors = new ArrayList<>();
        }
        validationErrors.add(new ValidationError(field, message));
    }
    
    // Constructor, getters, setters
}
```

**Using in service layer:**
```java
public Goal getGoal(Long goalId) {
    return goalRepository.findById(goalId)
        .orElseThrow(() -> new ResourceNotFoundException("Goal not found with id: " + goalId));
}

public Goal createGoal(Goal goal) {
    if(goalRepository.existsByTitleAndEmployeeId(goal.getTitle(), goal.getEmployeeId())) {
        throw new DuplicateResourceException("Goal with title '" + goal.getTitle() + "' already exists");
    }
    return goalRepository.save(goal);
}

public void approveGoal(Long goalId, Long managerId) {
    Goal goal = getGoal(goalId);
    
    if(!goal.getManagerId().equals(managerId)) {
        throw new AccessDeniedException("You are not authorized to approve this goal");
    }
    
    if(goal.getStatus().equals("APPROVED")) {
        throw new BusinessValidationException("Goal is already approved");
    }
    
    goal.setStatus("APPROVED");
    goalRepository.save(goal);
}
```

**Industry example:** In PerformanceTrack Analytics API:
- GET /analytics/goals/999 (goal doesn't exist) → 404 with "Goal not found"
- POST /analytics/goals (invalid date range) → 400 with validation errors
- PUT /analytics/goals/123/approve (not your goal) → 403 with "Access denied"
- POST /analytics/goals (goal title already exists) → 409 with "Duplicate goal"
- GET /analytics/department-metrics (database down) → 500 with "Service error"

