### Q80. How do we handle exceptions in @Scheduled methods?

Scheduled methods run automatically at intervals. Exceptions need special handling or they silently fail.

**Problem - Exception stops scheduling:**
```java
@Scheduled(fixedRate = 60000) // Every minute
public void generateReports() {
    int x = 10 / 0; // ArithmeticException
    // After this exception, scheduling STOPS for this method!
}
```

**Solution 1 - Try-catch inside scheduled method:**
```java
@Scheduled(fixedRate = 60000)
public void generateReports() {
    try {
        logger.info("Starting report generation");
        
        List<Report> reports = reportService.generateAll();
        
        logger.info("Generated {} reports", reports.size());
    } catch(Exception e) {
        logger.error("Report generation failed", e);
        // Notify admin
        sendAlert("Report generation failed: " + e.getMessage());
        // Scheduling continues!
    }
}
```

**Solution 2 - Global handler for scheduled methods:**
```java
@Configuration
public class SchedulerConfig implements SchedulingConfigurer {
    
    @Override
    public void configureTasks(ScheduledTaskRegistrar taskRegistrar) {
        taskRegistrar.setScheduler(taskExecutor());
    }
    
    @Bean
    public Executor taskExecutor() {
        ThreadPoolTaskScheduler scheduler = new ThreadPoolTaskScheduler();
        scheduler.setPoolSize(10);
        scheduler.setThreadNamePrefix("scheduled-task-");
        scheduler.setErrorHandler(t -> {
            logger.error("Scheduled task failed", t);
        });
        scheduler.initialize();
        return scheduler;
    }
}
```

**Solution 3 - Retry on failure:**
```java
@Scheduled(fixedRate = 300000) // Every 5 minutes
public void syncData() {
    int maxRetries = 3;
    int attempt = 0;
    
    while(attempt < maxRetries) {
        try {
            dataService.sync();
            logger.info("Data sync successful");
            return; // Success, exit
        } catch(Exception e) {
            attempt++;
            logger.warn("Data sync failed, attempt {}/{}", attempt, maxRetries, e);
            
            if(attempt >= maxRetries) {
                logger.error("Data sync failed after {} attempts", maxRetries, e);
                sendAlert("Data sync failed permanently");
            } else {
                // Wait before retry
                Thread.sleep(5000);
            }
        }
    }
}
```

**Conditional scheduling based on previous execution:**
```java
private boolean lastExecutionFailed = false;

@Scheduled(fixedRate = 60000)
public void processOrders() {
    if(lastExecutionFailed) {
        logger.warn("Skipping execution due to previous failure");
        return;
    }
    
    try {
        orderService.processAll();
        lastExecutionFailed = false;
    } catch(Exception e) {
        logger.error("Order processing failed", e);
        lastExecutionFailed = true;
        sendAlert("Order processing halted");
    }
}
```

**Industry example:** In PerformanceTrack, you have a scheduled job that calculates department-wise goal completion rates every night. If calculation fails (maybe database deadlock), you don't want job to stop permanently. You wrap in try-catch, log error, send email to admin with error details, and let scheduling continue. Next night, job runs again automatically.

