### Q89. How do we handle exceptions in event-driven architecture (Kafka, RabbitMQ)?

In message-driven systems, exception handling is different because there's no immediate caller to return error to.

**Problem - Message processing failure:**
```java
@KafkaListener(topics = "goal-approvals")
public void handleGoalApproval(GoalApprovalEvent event) {
    // What if this fails?
    // Message is lost!
    goalService.approveGoal(event.getGoalId());
}
```

**Solution 1 - Error handler with retry:**
```java
@KafkaListener(topics = "goal-approvals")
public void handleGoalApproval(GoalApprovalEvent event) {
    try {
        goalService.approveGoal(event.getGoalId());
        logger.info("Goal approved: {}", event.getGoalId());
    } catch(Exception e) {
        logger.error("Failed to approve goal: {}", event.getGoalId(), e);
        throw e; // Kafka will retry based on configuration
    }
}
```

**Solution 2 - Dead Letter Queue (DLQ):**
```java
@Configuration
public class KafkaErrorConfig {
    
    @Bean
    public ConcurrentKafkaListenerContainerFactory<String, GoalApprovalEvent> kafkaListenerContainerFactory() {
        ConcurrentKafkaListenerContainerFactory<String, GoalApprovalEvent> factory = 
            new ConcurrentKafkaListenerContainerFactory<>();
        
        // Configure error handler
        factory.setCommonErrorHandler(new DefaultErrorHandler(
            new DeadLetterPublishingRecoverer(kafkaTemplate()), // Send to DLQ
            new FixedBackOff(1000L, 3L) // Retry 3 times with 1 second gap
        ));
        
        return factory;
    }
}

@KafkaListener(topics = "goal-approvals")
public void handleGoalApproval(GoalApprovalEvent event) {
    // If this fails after 3 retries, message goes to DLQ
    goalService.approveGoal(event.getGoalId());
}

// Process messages from DLQ manually or with monitoring
@KafkaListener(topics = "goal-approvals.DLT") // Dead Letter Topic
public void handleFailedApprovals(GoalApprovalEvent event) {
    logger.error("Message failed permanently: {}", event);
    
    // Alert admin
    sendAlert("Goal approval failed for goal: " + event.getGoalId());
    
    // Save to database for manual investigation
    failedMessageRepository.save(event);
}
```

**Solution 3 - Idempotent processing (handle duplicates):**
```java
@KafkaListener(topics = "goal-approvals")
public void handleGoalApproval(GoalApprovalEvent event) {
    try {
        // Check if already processed (in case of retry)
        if(goalApprovalRepository.existsByGoalIdAndEventId(
            event.getGoalId(), 
            event.getEventId()
        )) {
            logger.info("Event already processed, skipping: {}", event.getEventId());
            return; // Idempotent - safe to receive duplicate
        }
        
        // Process
        goalService.approveGoal(event.getGoalId());
        
        // Mark as processed
        goalApprovalRepository.save(new ProcessedEvent(event.getEventId()));
        
    } catch(Exception e) {
        logger.error("Failed to process goal approval", e);
        throw e; // Will retry
    }
}
```

**Solution 4 - Compensating transaction on failure:**
```java
@KafkaListener(topics = "order-created")
public void handleOrderCreated(OrderEvent event) {
    try {
        // Reserve inventory
        inventoryService.reserve(event.getProductId(), event.getQuantity());
        
        // Process payment
        paymentService.charge(event.getAmount());
        
    } catch(PaymentException e) {
        logger.error("Payment failed, releasing inventory", e);
        
        // Compensate - release reserved inventory
        inventoryService.release(event.getProductId(), event.getQuantity());
        
        // Publish failure event
        kafkaTemplate.send("order-failed", new OrderFailedEvent(event.getOrderId(), e.getMessage()));
        
    } catch(Exception e) {
        logger.error("Order processing failed", e);
        throw e; // Retry
    }
}
```

**Solution 5 - Circuit breaker for external calls in listener:**
```java
@KafkaListener(topics = "notifications")
public void sendNotification(NotificationEvent event) {
    try {
        // Use circuit breaker for external email service
        circuitBreaker.executeSupplier(() -> {
            return emailService.send(event.getEmail(), event.getMessage());
        });
    } catch(CallNotPermittedException e) {
        // Circuit breaker OPEN - service down
        logger.warn("Email service down, saving to retry queue");
        retryQueue.save(event);
    } catch(Exception e) {
        logger.error("Notification failed", e);
        throw e; // Kafka will retry
    }
}
```

**Industry example:** In PerformanceTrack, when a goal is approved, event is published to "goal-approved" topic. Multiple listeners process it:
- Notification service sends email (if fails, retries 3 times, then DLQ)
- Analytics service updates metrics (idempotent - checks if already processed)
- Audit service logs event (never fails - writes to DLQ if database down)

Each listener has its own error handling strategy based on criticality.

